1
00:00:16,059 --> 00:00:19,062
At the left we can see...

2
00:00:19,229 --> 00:00:21,147
At the right we can see the...

3
00:00:21,147 --> 00:00:22,982
...the head-snarlers

4
00:00:23,066 --> 00:00:25,485
Everything is safe.
Perfectly safe.

5
00:00:25,652 --> 00:00:28,154
<i>Emo?</i>

6
00:00:29,280 --> 00:00:31,116
Watch out!

7
00:00:48,133 --> 00:00:49,634
Are you hurt?

8
00:00:53,096 --> 00:00:55,098
I don't think so.
You?

9
00:00:56,266 --> 00:00:58,143
I'm Ok.

10
00:00:58,226 --> 00:01:02,272
Get up.
Emo, it's not safe here.

11
00:01:03,148 --> 00:01:04,274
Let's go.

12
00:01:04,274 --> 00:01:06,276
What's next?

13
00:01:06,317 --> 00:01:10,321
You'll see!

14
00:01:17,162 --> 00:01:19,205
Emo.
This way.

15
00:01:35,388 --> 00:01:36,681
Follow me!

16
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:13,718
Hurry Emo!

17
00:02:49,295 --> 00:02:51,214
You're not paying attention!

18
00:02:51,381 --> 00:02:55,343
I just want to answer the...
...phone.

19
00:02:56,219 --> 00:02:59,264
Emo, look,
I mean listen.

20
00:03:00,473 --> 00:03:03,309
You have to learn to listen.

21
00:03:04,394 --> 00:03:06,271
This is not some game.

22
00:03:06,312 --> 00:03:10,650
You, I mean we,
we could easily die out here.

23
00:03:11,276 --> 00:03:15,280
Listen,
listen to the sounds of the machine.

24
00:03:19,325 --> 00:03:21,327
Listen to your breathing.

25
00:04:28,353 --> 00:04:30,355
Well, don't you ever get tired of this?

26
00:04:30,438 --> 00:04:32,315
Tired?!?

27
00:04:32,482 --> 00:04:35,902
Emo, the machine is like clockwork.

28
00:04:36,444 --> 00:04:38,488
One move out of place...

29
00:04:38,529 --> 00:04:40,531
...and you're ground to a pulp.

30
00:04:42,325 --> 00:04:43,409
But isn't it -

31
00:04:43,409 --> 00:04:47,455
Pulp, Emo!
Is that what you want, pulp?

32
00:04:48,414 --> 00:04:50,416
Emo, your goal in life...

33
00:04:51,459 --> 00:04:53,378
...pulp?

34
00:05:42,593 --> 00:05:44,512
Emo, close your eyes.

35
00:05:45,596 --> 00:05:47,515
Why?
- Now!

36
00:05:52,603 --> 00:05:53,604
<i>OK.</i>

37
00:05:54,564 --> 00:05:56,190
Good.

38
00:06:00,611 --> 00:06:03,614
What do you see at your left side, Emo?

39
00:06:05,491 --> 00:06:07,410
Nothing.
- Really?

40
00:06:07,493 --> 00:06:08,619
No, nothing at all.

41
00:06:09,412 --> 00:06:13,499
And at your right,
what do you see at your right side, Emo?

42
00:06:14,625 --> 00:06:17,628
The same Proog, exactly the same...

43
00:06:18,421 --> 00:06:20,631
...nothing!
- Great.

44
00:06:41,611 --> 00:06:44,280
Listen Proog! Do you hear that!

45
00:06:44,614 --> 00:06:46,449
Can we go here?

46
00:06:46,491 --> 00:06:49,452
There?
It isn't safe, Emo.

47
00:06:50,661 --> 00:06:53,581
But...
- Trust me, it's not.

48
00:06:54,540 --> 00:06:55,666
Maybe I could...

49
00:06:55,666 --> 00:06:57,543
No.

50
00:06:58,628 --> 00:07:01,547
NO!

51
00:07:01,672 --> 00:07:04,634
Any further questions, Emo?

52
00:07:05,510 --> 00:07:06,677
No.

53
00:07:10,598 --> 00:07:11,682
Emo?

54
00:07:12,683 --> 00:07:14,602
Emo, why...

55
00:07:14,602 --> 00:07:15,603
Emo...

56
00:07:15,603 --> 00:07:19,607
...why can't you see
the beauty of this place?

57
00:07:19,690 --> 00:07:21,651
The way it works.

58
00:07:21,692 --> 00:07:25,488
How perfect it is.

59
00:07:25,488 --> 00:07:28,574
No, Proog, I don't see.

60
00:07:28,616 --> 00:07:31,577
I don't see because there's nothing there.

61
00:07:32,620 --> 00:07:36,582
And why should I trust my
life to something that isn't there?

62
00:07:36,624 --> 00:07:38,543
Well can you tell me that?

63
00:07:38,626 --> 00:07:40,545
Answer me!

64
00:07:44,549 --> 00:07:45,633
Proog...

65
00:07:46,634 --> 00:07:48,594
...you're a sick man!

66
00:07:48,594 --> 00:07:50,555
Stay away from me!

67
00:07:53,641 --> 00:07:56,519
No! Emo! It's a trap!

68
00:07:56,727 --> 00:07:58,563
Hah, it's a trap.

69
00:07:58,563 --> 00:08:02,692
At the left side you can see
the hanging gardens of Babylon!

70
00:08:03,568 --> 00:08:05,611
How's that for a trap?

71
00:08:06,654 --> 00:08:08,573
No, Emo.

72
00:08:10,616 --> 00:08:13,744
At the right side you can see...
...well guess what...

73
00:08:14,537 --> 00:08:16,330
...the colossus of Rhodes!

74
00:08:16,747 --> 00:08:17,707
No!

75
00:08:17,707 --> 00:08:23,588
The colossus of Rhodes
and it is here just for you Proog.

76
00:08:52,658 --> 00:08:54,619
It is there...

77
00:08:54,619 --> 00:08:57,747
I'm telling you,
Emo...

78
00:08:58,664 --> 00:09:01,667
...it is.